                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-07T19:00:00-03:30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 7, 1926—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Your telegram number 23, October 2, 1 p.m. The Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    informed me today that Uruguay will be represented at the next meeting of the
                    Preliminary [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] Disarmament Commission, possibly by
                        Guani.<note n="6" xml:id="d89fn6">Alberto Guani. On Oct. 9 Mr. Grant-Smith
                        reported Uruguay’s Withdrawal from the Preparatory Commission.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
